{"cursor":"5148","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n{{Infobox artwork\n| image_file = Alliance on the Hayes, Cardiff.jpg image_size = 280px title =\n| Alliance alt = other_language_1 = other_title_1 = other_language_2 =\n| other_title_2 = artist = Jean-Bernard Metais year = type = Metal sculpture\n| dimensions = tall diameter city = The Hayes, Cardiff museum = pushpin_map\n| = Wales Cardiff Central pushpin_mapsize = 50 pushpin_map_caption=Location of\n| Alliance in Cardiff city centre latd = 51|latm = 28|lats = 40.8|latNS = N\n| longd = 3|longm = 10|longs = 31.44|longEW = W owner = St David's\n}}\n\n'Alliance' is a high sculpture in the centre of Cardiff, Wales. The sculpture\nconsists of a large stainless steel and enamelled metal arrow column and a hoop,\nwhich glows in the dark, and falls and rises with the tide.\n\nThe sculpture, paid for by the St Davidâs shopping centre as part of a Â£1.5m\npublic art scheme in the city centre, was installed in the space between the new\nmall and Cardiff Central Library in The Hayes area of the city centre. [http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/2009/12/03/arrow-\nart-aimed-at-the-heart-of-cardiff-s-history-and-culture-91466-25310297/\nWalesOnline | Arrow art aimed at the heart of Cardiffâs history and\nculture]\n","linknr":175,"url":"Alliance_(sculpture)","recorded":1374540623,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Alliance_(sculpture)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Alliance_(sculpture)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedi